SIMPLE: demagnetize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Demagnetize
<hw>De*mag"net*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To deprive of magnetic properties; to render nonmagnetic. See
<er>Magnetize</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If the bar be rapidly magnetized and <qex>demagnetized</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Am. Cyc.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To free from mesmeric influence; to
demesmerize.</def> <mark>[archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>De*mag`net*i*za"tion</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>De*mag"net*i`zer</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Demagog</ent>⟦br⟧
